President Muhammadu Buhari has again reassured that the Federal Government will soon end the attacks by bandits in northwest Nigeria. The president, therefore, appealed for the cooperation of state governments and security agencies across the country.
President Buhari commiserating with the government and people of Zamfara State on the infiltration of bandits who killed several innocent citizens in Tsafe Local Government Area, remarked that the bandits attacks are callous and despicable.
The Senior Special Assistant to the President on Media and Publicity, Garba Shehu, in a statement, indicated that President Buhari commended the new administration in the State for putting in new security measures to curtail the activities of criminals and bandits.
The President had encouraged the people of the state not to despair but to see the latest attack as a challenge to step up collective actions to rout the enemy, in partnership with the federal government. He issued order to the security personnel to take prompt and timely actions against the wicked attackers.








			
